<subSubSection id="10C4C8453D4A1EB5D7370EC95B5B1050" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="5817A32D30AE8FABB1E1A1AE8A70143D" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="550317F533B09B7E8C29F086B2FEDB56" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<taxonomicName id="46A244216345703A4554E0939E7D7683" authority="geryon" authorityName="geryon (Huebner" authorityYear="1813" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adscita geryon subsp. geryon" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryon" subSpecies="geryon">
<emphasis id="F0DCFB831A4A727E62227E90C2423428" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Adscita geryon geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed from the Iberian Peninsula and Britain to European Russia, the Crimea and Turkey. 
<bibRefCitation id="EC71845E6530B0B590573312F5EA58AD" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 61) reinstated the nominal taxon 
<taxonomicName id="6E41682ACCB998E04342FA52DA33BC89" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adscita geryon subsp. aeris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryon" subSpecies="aeris">
<emphasis id="24802C3F34FB72A59E4A2B9E66507259" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Adscita geryon aeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Verity, 1946) as valid and on the following page newly described a subspecies from the Paris region. It is acknowledged that 
<taxonomicName id="FB02FAB9F6E04ABA64C5007B4A66F91C" authority="Retzius, 1783" authorityName="Retzius" authorityYear="1783" baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1813" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adscita geryon" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geryon">
<emphasis id="35D79F6537344BA80E5DB9CA929D50EC" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Adscita geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extremely variable species, both in phenotype and genitalic morphology, but we see no justification for recalling a subspecies from synonymy, where it was placed by 
<bibRefCitation id="0828929D99A5CCE2A0ACBFE2F3405EAA" author="Efetov, KA" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B12" refString="Efetov, KA, Tarmann, GM, 1999. Forester Moths: The genera Theresimima Strand, 1917, Rhagades Wallengren, 1863, Jordanita Verity, 1946, and Adscita Retzius, 1783 (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae, Procridinae). Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Forester Moths: The genera Theresimima Strand, 1917, Rhagades Wallengren, 1863, Jordanita Verity, 1946, and Adscita Retzius, 1783 (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae, Procridinae)." year="1999">Efetov and Tarmann (1999</bibRefCitation>
: 28, 
<bibRefCitation id="ED05CB272B3D6A22D88699CD44A14845" author="Efetov, KA" journalOrPublisher="Crimean State University Press, Simferopol" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B13" refString="Efetov, KA, Tarmann, GM, 2012. A Checklist of the Palaearctic Procridinae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Crimean State University Press, Simferopol" title="A Checklist of the Palaearctic Procridinae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
: 31), or in describing a new subspecies from France. Accordingly, both taxa are here formally placed as synonyms (
<emphasis id="BE22F42EA63AF51519DBBB70CFBB8F82" bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">syn. rev.</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B6EB9190663BAE1B3E6F131CD338452D" bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">syn. n.</emphasis>
) of the nominotypical subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="660D6E6C5A15CE183CDF9D3E8CBE8C51" authority="geryon" authorityName="geryon (Huebner" authorityYear="1813" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Adscita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Adscita geryon subsp. geryon" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="geryon" subSpecies="geryon">
<emphasis id="8BFBED38EE931061AE4572AD2A170537" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Adscita geryon geryon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
